00:05:04,140 --> 00:05:14,090
And this is often referred to as outbound and inbound marketing.

84
00:05:14,090 --> 00:05:17,860
So what do we mean when we are going through these terms?

85
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:21,440
Well, push, or outbound, marketing communication

86
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:26,510
tends to refer to things which are typified by traditional paid

87
00:05:26,510 --> 00:05:30,380
advertising, like television, print, where

88
00:05:30,380 --> 00:05:37,210
we are pushing our message out to a large group of potential customers

89
00:05:37,210 --> 00:05:39,960
and then expecting a reaction.

90
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:43,290
The inbound, or pull, marketing tends to be

91
00:05:43,290 --> 00:05:50,070
more of a stimulated approach, which we will use often,

92
00:05:50,070 --> 00:05:52,950
direct mail, online email lists.

93
00:05:52,950 --> 00:05:57,800
We will be trying to get people to let us know that they're interested.

94
00:05:57,800 --> 00:06:00,300
And we can develop a relationship that way.

95
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:04,230
So it's not about right or wrong, although one sounds maybe

96
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:07,370
a little bit more traditional and one a little bit more contemporary.

97
00:06:07,370 --> 00:06:11,700
It's often about using a combination of the two,

98
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:16,060
depending on the stages that you are at in this framework.

